President Muhammadu Buhari has expressed his sympathy with the gas explosion victims in Kaduna, saying that his heart is with the victims at their hour of distress. President Buhari in a statement by his spokesman, Garba Shehu explained he was touched by the losses of life and economic ruin suffered by these “hard working Nigerians striving to make a living through honest labour.” “As a human being, I fully understand the economic impact of this accident on the lives of these hard working Nigerians”, the President declared sympathetically. President Buhari however advised Nigerians to pay greater attention to safety procedures and precautionary measures in their business places. According to him, precautionary measures can help to avert disasters.